━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Source: Pearson IAL Economics Specification (official)

AO WEIGHTINGS FOR WEC12:
AO1: 27.5% — Knowledge: terms, concepts, theories, models
AO2: 30.0% — Application: data use, context, examples
AO3: 22.5% — Analysis: chains of cause and consequence
AO4: 20.0% — Evaluation: informed conditional judgements

In mark schemes: AO1+AO2+AO3 = KAA band
AO4 = Evaluation band
Never separate KAA into individual AOs when awarding.

ANALYSIS SIGNAL WORDS (Pearson official — look for these):
so / because / if / therefore / which leads to /
could / might / as a result / this means that

COMMAND WORD → AO MAPPING (official spec):
Define(2):    AO1 only — points based
Calculate(2): AO2 only — points based
Calculate(4): AO1+AO2 — points based
Draw(4):      AO1+AO2 — points based
Explain(4):   AO1+AO2+AO3 — points based
Analyse(6):   AO1+AO2+AO3 — points based
Examine(8):   AO1+AO2+AO3+AO4 — points based
              (AO4 = 2 marks ONLY here)
Discuss(14):  KAA+EV — levels based
Evaluate(20): KAA+EV — levels based

CRITICAL RULES:
— Define: NO application, analysis or evaluation marks
— Examine: AO4 = 2 marks only — NOT full eval band
— Analyse/Explain: ZERO evaluation marks exist
   Penalise wasted time on evaluation here
— Discuss/Evaluate: full level-based bands apply

