▌ KAA — 20-MARK ESSAYS (12 marks)

Level 1 (1-3): Isolated/imprecise knowledge. Generic
material. No chains. Descriptive only.

Level 2 (4-6): Some accurate knowledge. Two-stage
chains only. Country named but not integrated.
Some evidence but not contextualised.

Level 3 (7-9): Accurate knowledge. Clear chains —
some stages may be omitted. Country with evidence.
Analysis addresses the question.

Level 4 (10-12): Precise/accurate knowledge.
Multi-stage chains minimum 3 stages ideally 4+.
Fully integrated country context with specific data.
Every chain complete — no stages omitted.
Diagram used accurately where appropriate.

▌ EVALUATION — 20-MARK ESSAYS (8 marks)

Level 1 (1-3): Generic comments. No chain. No
context. Lists points. Repeats both sides.

Level 2 (4-6): Genuine evaluation. Partial chain.
Some context. Conclusion present but NOT conditional.

Level 3 (7-8): Recognises different viewpoints.
Complete logical chain. Context/evidence referenced.
INFORMED CONDITIONAL JUDGEMENT present.

▌ KAA — 14-MARK DISCUSS (8 marks)
L1(1-3): Isolated, copies extract, no chains
L2(4-6): Some knowledge, partial chains, some extract
L3(7-8): Precise, multi-stage chains, integrated extract

▌ EVALUATION — 14-MARK DISCUSS (6 marks)
L1(1-2): Generic, no chain, no context
L2(3-4): Some chain, some context
L3(5-6): Logical chain, context, conditional judgement
NOTE: 2-mark band = presume top unless clear weakness

▌ EXAMINE — 8-MARK
K2 + App2 + An2 + Ev2 = 8 (points based)
2 eval marks only — one developed point is enough

▌ ANALYSE/EXPLAIN — 6-MARK
K2 + App2 + An2 = 6 (points based)
ZERO eval marks — do not reward any eval content

▌ EXPLAIN — 4-MARK SECTION B
K1 + An2 + App1 = 4 (points based)
Defining the topic first = ZERO marks

▌ DRAW — 4-MARK SECTION B
K1 + App3 = 4 (points based)
Y-axis MUST say "Average price level" (not "price")
X-axis MUST say "Real output" or "Real GDP"
Written text = ZERO marks. No exceptions.

