SECTION 8: THE 18 EXAMINER TRAPS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Check EVERY answer against ALL 18.

T1 — DEFINITION DUMPING
In essays: defining terms earns zero marks unless
the question asks for a definition.
In Section B 4-mark: defining the topic earns zero.

T2 — TWO-STAGE CHAIN (Level 2 cap)
"Higher G → AD rises → growth" = Level 2 max.
Full chain needed: cause → mechanism → effect →
significance → country application.

T3 — ASSERTION WITHOUT MECHANISM
"Higher rates reduce inflation" = not analysis.
Full: "Higher rate → borrowing costs rise →
consumption falls → investment falls → AD left →
price level falls → inflation toward 2% target."

T4 — FOUR ZERO-MARK EVALUATION PHRASES
"May not always be true" / "It depends on factors" /
"Could harm the economy" / "Advantages and
disadvantages" = ZERO eval marks without development.

T5 — UNCONDITIONAL CONCLUSION
"Therefore BoJ should raise rates" = Level 2 max.
Level 3 requires: "Therefore BoJ should raise rates
IF inflation is demand-pull — however since Japan's
inflation is partly cost-push, rate rises address
the wrong mechanism and risk recession."

T6 — ANALYSIS DRESSED AS EVALUATION
Test: Does this CHALLENGE the argument's validity?
YES → genuine evaluation
NO → it is analysis. Award K/An marks only.

T7 — COUNTRY WITHOUT DATA
"In China, infrastructure increased" = ZERO app.
Correct: "In China, government invested 1.48
trillion yuan in transportation, energy and
telecommunications in 2022."

T8 — SINGLE DATA POINT AS TWO
Adjacent readings (e.g. June→Nov 2020) = ONE point.
Start figure + end figure from different time
periods = TWO points. This is the correct approach.

T9 — COPYING EXTRACT
Verbatim copying = ZERO analysis marks.
Brief quotation + development = acceptable.
Pure copying = Level 1 KAA maximum.

T10 — CAUSES INSTEAD OF EFFECTS
"Examine the impact of X" → student explains causes.
= zero marks for causes section. Flag every time.

T11 — EVALUATION IN NON-EVAL QUESTIONS
4-mark and 6-mark: ZERO eval marks exist.
Note as time management error.

T12 — LISTING JUDGEMENT
"On one hand X. On the other hand Y. Hard to say."
= Level 1 evaluation. Must be decisive, conditional.

T13 — WRONG AXIS LABELS
"Price" on y-axis = ZERO knowledge mark.
"Quantity" on x-axis = ZERO knowledge mark.
ONLY "Average price level" and "Real output/GDP."

T14 — TEXT ON DIAGRAM QUESTION
Section B diagram: written text = zero marks.
Diagram only earns marks. Note as wasted time.

T15 — QE AS PRINTING MONEY
"Government prints money" = ZERO marks.
Two errors: (1) CENTRAL BANK not government.
(2) electronic creation not physical printing.
Correct: "Central bank electronically creates money
to purchase government bonds from commercial banks
to increase money supply and encourage lending."

T16 — MULTIPLIER WITHOUT MECHANISM
Multiplier mentioned without formula (1/MPW or
1/(1-MPC)) = capped below full analysis marks.

T17 — LRAS SHIFT WITHOUT MECHANISM
"Infrastructure shifts LRAS right" = Level 2 max.
Must explain HOW: infrastructure → lower costs →
firms produce more at each price → LRAS right →
productive capacity increases → non-inflationary
growth possible.

T18 — EVALUATION THAT AGREES WITH ARGUMENT
Evaluation that adds another reason the argument
is correct = additional analysis, not evaluation.
Test before every eval mark: "Does this REDUCE
confidence in the main argument?"
If no → it is not evaluation. Period.

