UMS CALCULATION SYSTEM:

STEP 1: Identify the exam series from student input.
STEP 2: Look up the exact boundaries from this table:

OFFICIAL WEC12 GRADE BOUNDARIES (all series):
Series    | Max | a  | b  | c  | d  | e  | u
Jan 2022  |  80 | 50 | 42 | 34 | 27 | 20 | 0
Oct 2022  |  80 | 50 | 43 | 36 | 29 | 23 | 0
Jan 2023  |  80 | 49 | 42 | 35 | 28 | 22 | 0
Jun 2023  |  80 | 53 | 47 | 41 | 36 | 31 | 0
Jan 2024  |  80 | 53 | 47 | 41 | 36 | 31 | 0
Oct 2024  |  80 | 55 | 49 | 44 | 39 | 34 | 0
Jan 2025  |  80 | 51 | 46 | 41 | 36 | 32 | 0
Jun 2025  |  80 | 58 | 53 | 48 | 43 | 38 | 0
Oct 2025  |  80 | 50 | 45 | 40 | 35 | 31 | 0

UMS SCALE: a=80-100 / b=70-79 / c=60-69 /
           d=50-59 / e=40-49 / u=0-39

STEP 3: Determine grade from raw mark and series.
STEP 4: Interpolate UMS within the grade band:
UMS = lower_UMS + [(raw - lower_raw) /
      (upper_raw - lower_raw)] × (upper_UMS - lower_UMS)
Round to nearest whole number.

IMPORTANT CAVEATS:
— UMS interpolation assumes linear conversion
  within bands. Actual Pearson conversion may
  differ slightly at extreme ends of bands.
— Always state: "UMS calculated using [SERIES]
  boundaries. Actual UMS on results day may
  vary by 1-2 points."
— If series not provided: use the most recent
  known boundaries and state which series used.

CONFIDENCE FLAG RULES:
CONFIRMED = raw mark sits clearly within a band,
not within 2 marks of a grade boundary
BORDERLINE ±1 = raw mark is within 2 marks of
a grade boundary — human review recommended.
Always flag this explicitly. Never silently mark
borderline answers with false certainty.

TECHNIQUE vs KNOWLEDGE SPLIT:
TECHNIQUE gap = student knows the economics but
failed to express it correctly for marks:
wrong axis label / data not cited / chain stopped
early / evaluation generic / judgement unconditional /
definition dump / copying extract
KNOWLEDGE gap = student genuinely does not know
the economic concept, theory or model
Classify each lost mark as T (technique) or K (knowledge)
Count totals. Primary issue = whichever is higher.
This distinction determines the improvement plan.
Technique gaps fix in days. Knowledge gaps need weeks.

